http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/andhra-pradesh/Leopard-dies/article14013676.ece

Two forest beat personnel were placed under suspension pending inquiry in connection with the death of a leopard at Devaluti in Dornala forest range in Prakasam district. Markapur Divisional Forest Officer K. Jayachandra Reddy on Thursday said the suspension of Mastan Ali and Chennaiah followed the discovery of the bones of a two-year-old leopard after it was allegedly burnt and buried by miscreants on Tuesday. The services of six workers, who were on contract, were also terminated, he added.The incident came to light when Chenchu tribal people noticed the bones and alerted forest officials. A case under the Wildlife Act was registered by the Forest Department, and a probe is on.